ead I/O consumption \n- node disk write I/O consumption \n- node disk space consumption\n\nAnomaly Cluster Description:\nThe cluster spans 23 minutes (09:30-09:53) and contains 69 related anomalies. Issues began with frontend-http request rate anomalies at 09:30, followed by container file descriptor problems on node-5.frontend-2 starting at 09:32. The adservice experienced garbage collection memory issues throughout the period. Network problems emerged with TCP retransmissions on node-5. Communication anomalies appeared between frontend-checkoutservice and frontend-currencyservice via gRPC. Log errors in adservice started later at 09:38 and continued through the incident, coinciding with increased duration in currency service calls. The sustained file descriptor issues (13 consecutive minutes) and network problems likely contributed to the cascading failures across services.\n\nRelevant Historical Incidents (if any):\nNone\n\nBackgroud:\n"\n\n\nBased on this information, identify the MOST LIKELY root cause component and reason from the candidate list.\nFollow these rules:\n- The root cause must be a single component from the candidate list.\n- The reason must be directly supported by the anomaly description.\n- Assign a suspicious score between 0.0 and 1.0 (higher = more confident).\n\nRespond ONLY with a JSON object in this exact format:\n{\n    "component": "service-name",\n    "reason": "brief reason",\n    "score": 0.92\n}'}]
