e disk write I/O consumption \n- node disk space consumption\n\nAnomaly Cluster Description:\nThe root cause appears to be CPU scheduling issues in the frontend container (node-5.frontend-0) that started at 11:14:00 and persisted for 6 minutes. This issue triggered a cascade effect across the system: first affecting trace frequency between frontend2-0 and currencyservice2-0 at 11:15:00, then causing request duration anomalies in the istio-egressgateway at 11:16:00-11:17:00, followed by memory anomalies on node-2 at 11:17:00 and 11:20:00, and finally causing non-heap memory issues in the adservice at 11:18:00-11:19:00. The frontend container, being upstream in the service dependency chain, was the initial point of failure that impacted downstream services.\n\nRelevant Historical Incidents (if any):\nNone\n\nBackgroud:\n"\n\n\nBased on this information, identify the MOST LIKELY root cause component and reason from the candidate list.\nFollow these rules:\n- The root cause must be a single component from the candidate list.\n- The reason must be directly supported by the anomaly description.\n- Assign a suspicious score between 0.0 and 1.0 (higher = more confident).\n\nRespond ONLY with a JSON object in this exact format:\n{\n    "component": "service-name",\n    "reason": "brief reason",\n    "score": 0.92\n}'}]
