read I/O consumption \n- node disk write I/O consumption \n- node disk space consumption\n\nAnomaly Cluster Description:\nThe primary issue was high system load on node-2 starting at 19:00, which cascaded to multiple services. The currencyservice-1 experienced HTTP retry errors, likely due to connectivity issues from the node load. This affected adservice components with garbage collection anomalies and unusual HTTP 302 redirect traffic between frontend and adservice. The sustained 14-minute event spanned multiple system layers, indicating infrastructure strain propagating through the service mesh.\n\nRelevant Historical Incidents (if any):\nNone\n\nBackgroud:\n"\n\n\nBased on this information, identify the MOST LIKELY root cause component and reason from the candidate list.\nFollow these rules:\n- The root cause must be a single component from the candidate list.\n- The reason must be directly supported by the anomaly description.\n- Assign a suspicious score between 0.0 and 1.0 (higher = more confident).\n\nRespond ONLY with a JSON object in this exact format:\n{\n    "component": "service-name",\n    "reason": "brief reason",\n    "score": 0.92\n}'}]
